# `@needle/ui-web` + `apps/studio`

The browser-viewable, reusable design system and its demo. Background and the
locked decisions: `docs/v2/studio-redesign.md` and
`docs/decisions/2026-05-31-ui-web-studio-redesign.md`. **Read those first.**

## Non-negotiables

- **One canonical model; templates are pure presentation config.** A template is a
  config object (`Template` in `src/model/template.ts`). Switching or building a
  template MUST NOT mutate item data — layout renderers receive `TodayItemView[]` +
  a `Template` and only read. This is the open/closed core; do not break it.
- **Reuse `@needle/domain`.** Entities (`Item`, `ItemPlan`, `ItemOccurrence`,
  `ItemRelation`, `Suggestion`, `Intervention`, `TodayItemView`, …) come from
  `@needle/domain/domain-v2`, re-exported via `src/model/domain.ts`. Do NOT invent a
  parallel entity that already exists there. New UI-driven types go in `src/model/*`
  with a "promote into @needle/domain once validated" comment.
- **`src/model/index.ts` is the one allowed barrel** — the curated public surface and
  "one place to see every moving part." This is a deliberate exception to
  `typescript.mdc` (no barrels), which targets the Electron renderer. Do not add other
  barrels casually.
- **Pure logic stays pure.** Everything in `src/model/*` (except component files) is
  framework-free, no React, no I/O — so it's unit-testable. Keep it that way; put a
  `*.test.ts` beside new logic (Vitest, per `testing.mdc`).

## Styling

- Follow `design-tokens.mdc`, `design-primitives.mdc`, `design-components.mdc`,
  `design-dark-mode.mdc`. **Semantic tokens only** (`var(--ink)`, `var(--surface)`,
  `var(--urgent)`…) — never raw hex, never `--sand-*`/`--ink-*` primitives in
  components. Spacing on the ×4 scale; radii 4/6/8/12/16/999.
- The package is **self-contained**: tokens in `src/styles/{primitives,tokens,base}.css`,
  fonts via `@fontsource` in `src/styles/index.ts`. Consumers do
  `import '@needle/ui-web/styles'` once at app root. Every component ships its CSS
  beside it (`Foo.tsx` + `Foo.css`).
- Both themes must work; verify light AND dark. Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## React / TS

- Function components, `type Props` above the component, named exports, no `React.FC`
  (`react.mdc`). Strict TS with `exactOptionalPropertyTypes` — build optional props
  with conditional spreads (`...(x ? { x } : {})`), never assign `undefined`.
- Variant unions, not boolean-flag soup; all interactive states
  (default/hover/focus/active/disabled); `aria-label` + `:focus-visible`.

## Studio (`apps/studio`)

- Demo harness only. App/feature styling lives in `ui-web`; `studio.css` is just the
  rail/topbar/content chrome. New scenarios mount real `ui-web` components — don't
  reimplement features in studio.

## Runtime ids (persisted consumers)

- Ids come from `uid()` (`model/ids.ts`) — a **per-process counter that resets to 0
  on reload**. Any app that loads a persisted `TodayData` (e.g. `apps/desktop` from
  SQLite) MUST call **`reserveIdsFromData(loaded)`** right after loading, before any
  `addItem`/`addChild`/`addEvent`. Skip it and a freshly minted id can duplicate a
  loaded one — `childrenOf` then resolves a new child to a *different* existing item,
  and the persistence layer rejects the duplicate primary key.

## Consuming this package (desktop)

- `@needle/ui-web` is live-edited, so it is excluded from the desktop renderer's Vite
  pre-bundling (`apps/desktop/vite.renderer.config.ts` `optimizeDeps.exclude`). If
  ui-web edits don't appear in the desktop app, or the window goes blank after you add
  an export, the Vite dep cache is stale — see `build-and-tooling.mdc` (clear
  `apps/desktop/node_modules/.vite`, restart).

## Verify

```bash
pnpm --filter @needle/ui-web typecheck && pnpm --filter @needle/ui-web test
pnpm --filter @needle/studio dev   # click through, toggle light/dark
```

Relevant skills: `needle-build-component`, `needle-design-system`, `needle-add-token`,
`needle-dark-mode-fix`, `needle-ui-audit`.
